influence on artistic careers and the prospects of Hollywood’s forthcoming projects. Agents are crucial to understanding how creative and economic power are intertwined in Hollywood today. They play a key role in the process by which artistic worth and economic value are evaluated and attributed to people and projects. Roussel’s fieldwork examines what “having relationships” really means for agents, and how they perform the relationship work that’s at the heart of their professional existence and success. Representing Talent helps us to understand the players behind the definition of entertainment itself, as well as behind its current transformations.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aMotion picture industryzUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aTheatrical agencies - California - History. 0aTheatrical agencieszCaliforniaxHistory. 0aTheatrical agentszCaliforniaxHistory. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  aHollywood.  aartistic careers.  acultural brokerage.  acultural markets.  acultural sociology.  afilm production.  asocial networks.  asociology of work.  atalent agencies.  atalent agents.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z97831107119360 cprintz978022648680240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226487137423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226487137/original  a978-3-11-071193-6  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles